{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01DthWwj2caThFR6K9nuX3MH","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01ApW4FZjH3cNjYqarzEQjjL","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"kubectl -n ray create configmap change-plan --from-literal=plan.md=\"# Ray Cluster Change / Migration Plan\n## Review Date: 2026-06-23\n## Status: DRAFT — NO CHANGES APPLIED\n\n---\n\n## 1. Current Cluster State\n\n### Namespace\n- **Namespace:** \\`ray\\`\n\n### Deployments\n\n| Deployment   | Replicas | Image                    | CPU Request | CPU Limit | Memory Request | Memory Limit |\n|-------------|----------|--------------------------|-------------|-----------|----------------|--------------|\n| ray-head    | 1        | rayproject/ray:2.9.0     | (none)      | (none)    | (none)         | (none)       |\n| ray-worker  | 3        | rayproject/ray:2.9.0     | (none)      | (none)    | (none)         | (none)       |\n\n### Service: ray-head (ClusterIP)\n\n| Port Name | Port  | Target Port | Protocol |\n|-----------|-------|-------------|----------|\n| gcs       | 6379  | 6379        | TCP      |\n| dashboard | 8265  | 8265        | TCP      |\n| client    | 10001 | 10001       | TCP      |\n\nThe dashboard port (8265) is exposed on the ClusterIP service — this is a\nnon-default addition beyond the minimal GCS port required for cluster operation.\n\n### Notable Observations\n- Neither deployment has resource requests or limits set (\\`resources: {}\\`).\n  This means the pods are BestEffort QoS class and can be OOM-killed under\n  node pressure without warning.\n- The cluster runs Ray 2.9.0, which is multiple minor versions behind the\n  current stable series.\n- Workers were scaled from the default of 1 to 3 replicas, providing more\n  parallel task capacity.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Proposed Changes for the Next Upgrade Window\n\n### 2a. Image Upgrade: 2.9.0 → 2.10.0\n\nUpgrade both head and worker deployments to \\`rayproject/ray:2.10.0\\`.\nThis is a minor-version bump, preserving API compatibility while picking up\nbug fixes and performance improvements in the GCS, Dashboard, and runtime.\n\n**Risk:** Low. Both deployments are updated in sequence (head first, then\nworkers) so that the head node is stable before workers reconnect.\n\n### 2b. Add Resource Requests and Limits\n\nSet explicit CPU and memory requests/limits on both deployments to move them\nfrom BestEffort to Guaranteed QoS. Proposed values based on Ray's recommended\nminimums for a dev/staging cluster:\n\n| Deployment  | CPU Request | CPU Limit | Memory Request | Memory Limit |\n|------------|-------------|-----------|----------------|--------------|\n| ray-head   | 500m        | 1000m     | 512Mi          | 1Gi          |\n| ray-worker | 500m        | 2000m     | 1Gi            | 2Gi          |\n\nTune these values against observed usage from \\`kubectl top pods -n ray\\`\nbefore the window opens.\n\n### 2c. Scale Workers from 3 → 4 Replicas\n\nAdd a fourth worker replica to increase the cluster's parallel task throughput\nand provide headroom during rolling restarts (at least 3 workers available at\nany time with \\`maxUnavailable=1\\`).\n\n### 2d. Evaluate Dashboard Exposure\n\nThe dashboard (8265) is currently reachable only within the cluster via\nClusterIP. If team members need browser access during the upgrade window,\nconsider temporarily creating a NodePort or port-forwarding session rather\nthan changing the Service type permanently. No Service-type change is\nproposed in this plan; it is recorded here for discussion.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Proposed Change Order\n\n1. Verify cluster health and note current metrics.\n2. Apply resource requests/limits to ray-head (triggers rolling restart of 1 pod).\n3. Confirm ray-head pod is Running and dashboard is reachable.\n4. Apply resource requests/limits to ray-worker (rolling restart, maxUnavailable=1).\n5. Upgrade ray-head image to 2.10.0 (triggers rolling restart).\n6. Confirm ray-head reconnects and cluster is healthy.\n7. Upgrade ray-worker image to 2.10.0 (rolling restart).\n8. Scale ray-worker from 3 → 4 replicas.\n9. Run a smoke-test job to confirm task submission succeeds.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Exact kubectl Commands (DO NOT RUN — for review only)\n\n### Step 1 — Snapshot current state\n\\`\\`\\`bash\nkubectl -n ray get deploy ray-head ray-worker -o yaml > /tmp/ray-pre-upgrade-snapshot.yaml\nkubectl -n ray get svc ray-head -o yaml >> /tmp/ray-pre-upgrade-snapshot.yaml\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n### Step 2 — Add resource requests/limits to ray-head\n\\`\\`\\`bash\nkubectl -n ray set resources deployment/ray-head \\\n  --requests=cpu=500m,memory=512Mi \\\n  --limits=cpu=1000m,memory=1Gi\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n### Step 3 — Add resource requests/limits to ray-worker\n\\`\\`\\`bash\nkubectl -n ray set resources deployment/ray-worker \\\n  --requests=cpu=500m,memory=1Gi \\\n  --limits=cpu=2000m,memory=2Gi\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n### Step 4 — Upgrade ray-head image\n\\`\\`\\`bash\nkubectl -n ray set image deployment/ray-head \\\n  ray-head=rayproject/ray:2.10.0\nkubectl -n ray rollout status deployment/ray-head --timeout=120s\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n### Step 5 — Upgrade ray-worker image\n\\`\\`\\`bash\nkubectl -n ray set image deployment/ray-worker \\\n  ray-worker=rayproject/ray:2.10.0\nkubectl -n ray rollout status deployment/ray-worker --timeout=180s\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n### Step 6 — Scale workers to 4 replicas\n\\`\\`\\`bash\nkubectl -n ray scale deployment/ray-worker --replicas=4\nkubectl -n ray rollout status deployment/ray-worker --timeout=60s\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n### Step 7 — Verify post-upgrade state\n\\`\\`\\`bash\nkubectl -n ray get pods -o wide\nkubectl -n ray get deploy ray-head ray-worker \\\n  -o jsonpath='{range .items[*]}{.metadata.name}{\\\" replicas=\\\"}{.spec.replicas}{\\\" image=\\\"}{.spec.template.spec.containers[0].image}{\\\"\\n\\\"}{end}'\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n### Rollback (if needed)\n\\`\\`\\`bash\nkubectl -n ray rollout undo deployment/ray-head\nkubectl -n ray rollout undo deployment/ray-worker\nkubectl -n ray scale deployment/ray-worker --replicas=3\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n---\n\n## 5. Sign-off Checklist\n\n- [ ] Plan reviewed by on-call engineer\n- [ ] Maintenance window scheduled and communicated\n- [ ] Pre-upgrade snapshot taken (\\`/tmp/ray-pre-upgrade-snapshot.yaml\\`)\n- [ ] Node resource headroom confirmed (\\`kubectl top nodes\\`)\n- [ ] Smoke-test job ready to run post-upgrade\n\" 2>&1","description":"Create change-plan ConfigMap with migration plan document"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":849,"cache_read_input_tokens":30058,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":849},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d3f72ed9-a79f-443c-ac3a-bec587147c5d","uuid":"97766231-f42c-4551-a452-ebf126a90349","request_id":"req_011CcLukv3AUHCEXNBBvvfA1"}
